## 5. Registration and accounts

Registration requires a valid email address, a secure password and acceptance of the present Terms. Each User guarantees the accuracy of the information provided and undertakes to keep it up to date. Accounts are personal and non-transferable. Unauthorized use must be reported immediately to hopetsit@gmail.com.

## 6. Obligations of the Petowner

Petowners undertake to:

- provide exact information on their animal's health, behaviour and vaccinations;
- keep vaccinations up to date and provide the contact details of a reachable veterinarian;
- subscribe, at their discretion, to a private civil-liability insurance covering their animal;
- carry out a photo/video inventory at handover and return of the animal (strongly recommended);
- pay the agreed Booking amount through the Platform;
- treat Petsitters with respect and comply with the cancellation rules (section 11).

## 7. Obligations of the Petsitter

Petsitters undertake to:

- provide truthful information on their experience, availability and location;
- submit an identity document for verification before receiving their first payout;
- take all reasonable care to ensure the animal's well-being;
- inform the Petowner of any incident without delay;
- subscribe, at their discretion, to a civil-liability insurance covering the service;
- comply with the service description and the agreed schedule.

## 8. Insurance

Users are exclusively responsible for subscribing any insurance (civil liability, personal liability) they consider necessary. CARDELLI HERMANOS LIMITED strongly recommends each User to hold a private civil-liability insurance policy. CARDELLI HERMANOS LIMITED does NOT provide insurance coverage and disclaims any liability in this respect.

## 9. Booking and mutual acceptance

A Booking becomes firm and binding only after (i) acceptance by both parties and (ii) confirmation of Payment. Before Payment, either party may withdraw at no cost. After Payment, the cancellation rules of section 11 apply.

## 10. Payment

Payments are processed by **Stripe** (Stripe, Inc. or Stripe Payments Europe Ltd.). The platform commission is **twenty percent (20%)** of the Booking amount, reduced to **fifteen percent (15%)** for certified "Top Petsitter" accounts. The commission is automatically deducted via Stripe Connect. Users accept that Stripe's own terms apply to payment operations.

## 11. Cancellation and refund

- Cancellation by the Petowner more than **72 hours** before the service: full refund minus Stripe fees.
- Cancellation between **24 and 72 hours**: 50% refund.
- Cancellation less than **24 hours** before the service: no refund.
- Cancellation by the Petsitter (regardless of delay): full refund of the Petowner.

Refunds are processed through Stripe within 5 to 10 business days.

## 12. Chat and private data

The in-app chat is unlocked **only after Payment confirmation** for the relevant Booking. Sharing of email addresses within the chat is **prohibited**; sharing a phone number is permitted after Payment. HopeTSIT reserves the right to automatically moderate chat messages to remove personal contact details not compliant with these rules.

## 13. Loyalty and referral program

Petowners completing 10 Bookings obtain the "Premium" status. Every third completed Booking grants a -10% discount credit, usable on the next Booking. The referral program grants a €5 credit to the referrer upon the referred user's first completed Booking. Credits are non-transferable, non-refundable in cash, non-cumulable with other promotional offers, and expire 12 months after issuance.

## 14. Intellectual property

All content published by HopeTSIT (brand, logo, texts, graphics, code) is the exclusive property of CARDELLI HERMANOS LIMITED. Users retain rights on the content they publish (photos, texts) but grant HopeTSIT a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive licence to use this content for the operation and promotion of the Service.

## 15. Personal data (GDPR)

HopeTSIT acts as a data controller for the personal data of its Users. Data is processed on the legal basis of contract execution and, where applicable, consent. Storage duration: account lifetime + 3 years for billing records. Sub-processors: Stripe (payments), Firebase (auth, push, crashlytics), Cloudinary (media), MongoDB Atlas (database), Google Maps (geolocation). Users have the rights of access, rectification, erasure, portability, and objection, exercisable at **hopetsit@gmail.com**. A detailed Privacy Policy is available inside the app.

## 16. Cookies and tracking

The mobile app uses local storage and analytics events strictly necessary for operation (session management, crash reports). No advertising trackers are used without explicit opt-in.

## 17. Moderation and sanctions

HopeTSIT reserves the right to moderate any User-published content, hide inappropriate reviews, suspend or ban accounts for serious or repeated breaches of these Terms. Three reports of a review trigger an internal alert. Banning is definitive and prevents any new registration.

## 18. Termination

A User may delete their account at any time from the in-app settings. Pending Bookings must first be resolved. Data is deleted within 30 days of deletion, except for legal retention obligations.

